In [7]:
# Step 4: Handling Missing Values

# 1️⃣ Check missing values again
print("Missing Values in Each Column:")
print(df.isnull().sum())

# 2️⃣ Drop columns with too many missing values (if applicable)
# Since 'aspect_ratio' and 'content_rating' are missing, we skip them

# 3️⃣ Fill missing values for numerical columns with the median
num_cols = df.select_dtypes(include=['number']).columns  # Select numeric columns
df[num_cols] = df[num_cols].fillna(df[num_cols].median())

# 4️⃣ Fill missing values for categorical columns with mode (most frequent value)
cat_cols = df.select_dtypes(include=['object']).columns  # Select categorical columns
df[cat_cols] = df[cat_cols].fillna(df[cat_cols].mode().iloc[0])

# 5️⃣ Verify if missing values are handled
print("\nUpdated Missing Values Count:")
print(df.isnull().sum())

# Display updated dataset info

# Splitting the 'genres' column and counting each genre

# Plotting the top genres
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
sns.barplot(x=genre_counts.index[:10], y=genre_counts.values[:10], hue=genre_counts.index[:10], 
            dodge=False, legend=False, palette="viridis")  # Fixing the warning
plt.xticks(rotation=45)
plt.xlabel("Genres")
plt.ylabel("Number of Movies")
plt.title("Top 10 Most Common Movie Genres")
plt.show()
